    public class BranchEmployee
extends Customer
    This class is about branch employee operations Branch employee extends customer, so it has all authorities of customer

      void addCustomer(java.util.ArrayList<User> accounts, java.util.ArrayList<Branch> branches)
      Branch employee can add customer by entering name, surname, email, password, address, phonenumber If the entered email address is wrong, branch employee can not add customer When the customer is added, system assigned a customer id to the customer automatically
      void addProduct(java.util.ArrayList<Product> products)
      Branch employee can add product by entering category, model, color If the entered category name is same with an existing category, branch employee can not add product When product is added, system assigned a product id to the product automatically
      void decreaseProductAmount(java.util.ArrayList<Product> products)
      Branch employee can decrease amount of products by entering category, model, color If the branch employee enters a product does not exist, can not decrease its amount

      void listProductsOutStock(java.util.ArrayList<Product> products, int requestedAmount)

      void makeSale(java.util.ArrayList<User> accounts, java.util.ArrayList<Product> products, java.util.ArrayList<Order> orders)
      Branch employee can make sale in store or online by entering customer id and product id to sell If the entered customer id or product id is wrong, branch employee can not make sale When sale is done, system creates an order automatically and assigns an order id to this order Orders keeps informations of sale, customer and product ids
      void removeCustomer(java.util.ArrayList<User> accounts)
      Branch employee can remove customer by entering customer id If the entered customer id is wrong, branch employee can not remove customer
      void removeProduct(java.util.ArrayList<Product> products)
